Note:
==============================================================================
CAPABILITY - Unforgeable capability token for authorization
==============================================================================

A Capability is a cryptographically-bound authorization token. The
holder of a valid Capability has proven they can perform the named
operation on the named scope until the named expiration. The token
carries an Ed25519 signature; verification requires the public key
of the issuing authority.

Field layout in the SIGNED PAYLOAD (canonical encoding):
  +-- operation_id (8 bytes, big-endian integer)
  +-- scope_hash   (32 bytes; SHA-256 of the scope string)
  +-- issued_at    (8 bytes, Unix seconds, big-endian)
  +-- expiration   (8 bytes, Unix seconds, big-endian)
  +-- nonce        (16 bytes, random; per-token uniqueness)

Total payload = 72 bytes.

Memory layout of the Capability struct itself (48 bytes):
  offset  0 : operation_id   (8 bytes)
  offset  8 : scope_hash ptr (8 bytes; into arena)
  offset 16 : issued_at      (8 bytes)
  offset 24 : expiration     (8 bytes)
  offset 32 : nonce ptr      (8 bytes; into arena)
  offset 40 : signature ptr  (8 bytes; into arena; 64-byte Ed25519 sig)

The signature is over the canonical-encoded 72-byte payload.

References:
- Dennis & Van Horn, "Programming Semantics for Multiprogrammed
  Computations", CACM 1966 (capability-based security origin).
- Macaroons (Birgisson et al. 2014): caveat-extensible capabilities.
- RFC 6749 OAuth 2.0: bearer tokens.
- RFC 7519: JWT (a degenerate-form capability).
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/crypto_identity/crypto_algorithm.runa" as Alg
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/crypto_identity/public_key.runa" as PK
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/crypto_identity/private_key.runa" as SK
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/crypto_identity/signature.runa" as Sig
Import "runtime/core/memory/arena.runa" as Arena
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/sha2.runa" as Sha2
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/entropy.runa" as Entropy
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/secure_memory.runa" as Secure

Let CAPABILITY_STRUCT_SIZE be 48
Let CAP_OFF_OPERATION be 0
Let CAP_OFF_SCOPE_HASH be 8
Let CAP_OFF_ISSUED_AT be 16
Let CAP_OFF_EXPIRATION be 24
Let CAP_OFF_NONCE be 32
Let CAP_OFF_SIGNATURE be 40

Let CAP_PAYLOAD_SIZE be 72
Let CAP_SCOPE_HASH_SIZE be 32
Let CAP_NONCE_SIZE be 16

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SECTION 1: Canonical encoding
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Encode the capability payload bytes for signing. Output is exactly
72 bytes, written into out_buffer at offset 0.

Big-endian integer encoding is used throughout so the canonical bytes
are byte-order-independent. The Network and persistence layers see the
same bytes regardless of platform endianness.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Steps:
  1. Validate buffers.
  2. Write operation_id as 8 bytes big-endian.
  3. Copy scope_hash (32 bytes) at offset 8.
  4. Write issued_at as 8 bytes big-endian at offset 40.
  5. Write expiration as 8 bytes big-endian at offset 48.
  6. Copy nonce (16 bytes) at offset 56.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(payload size = 72). Constant cost.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The canonical encoding must be exact across producers and verifiers;
any divergence breaks signature verification. Field ordering matches
the FIELD LAYOUT comment in the module header and MUST NOT be
changed without bumping a version field (which v0.0.8.5 does not yet
include; downstream "Capability v2" extensions will).
@End Security_Scope
Process called "capability_encode_payload" takes operation_id as Integer, scope_hash_32 as Integer, issued_at as Integer, expiration as Integer, nonce_16 as Integer, out_buffer as Integer returns Integer:
    If out_buffer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If scope_hash_32 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If nonce_16 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: operation_id big-endian, 8 bytes.
    Let op_v be operation_id
    Let oi be 7
    Let oc be 0
    While oc is less than 8:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buffer, oi, op_v modulo by 256)
        Set op_v to op_v divided by 256
        Set oi to oi minus 1
        Set oc to oc plus 1
    End While

    Note: scope_hash 32 bytes at offset 8.
    Memory.memory_copy(out_buffer plus 8, scope_hash_32, CAP_SCOPE_HASH_SIZE)

    Note: issued_at big-endian, 8 bytes at offset 40.
    Let ia_v be issued_at
    Let ii be 47
    Let ic be 0
    While ic is less than 8:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buffer, ii, ia_v modulo by 256)
        Set ia_v to ia_v divided by 256
        Set ii to ii minus 1
        Set ic to ic plus 1
    End While

    Note: expiration big-endian, 8 bytes at offset 48.
    Let ex_v be expiration
    Let xi be 55
    Let xc be 0
    While xc is less than 8:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buffer, xi, ex_v modulo by 256)
        Set ex_v to ex_v divided by 256
        Set xi to xi minus 1
        Set xc to xc plus 1
    End While

    Note: nonce 16 bytes at offset 56.
    Memory.memory_copy(out_buffer plus 56, nonce_16, CAP_NONCE_SIZE)
    Return CAP_PAYLOAD_SIZE
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SECTION 2: capability_grant - issue and sign
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Issue a new Capability granting holder permission to perform
operation_id on scope (any byte string) until expiration. The scope is
hashed with SHA-256 to produce a 32-byte commitment; the full scope
string need not be transported with the token (verification can
recompute the hash).

The token is signed with issuing_private_key, which MUST be the
Ed25519 private key of the issuing authority. Other signature
algorithms are rejected; the Capability primitive uses Ed25519
exclusively for simplicity and to keep verification cost minimal
(~100us on x86-64).

A 16-byte random nonce is included to ensure token uniqueness even
across same-(op, scope, issued_at, expiration) issuances.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Steps:
  1. Validate inputs.
  2. Verify issuing_private_key.algorithm == ALG_ED25519.
  3. Allocate scope_hash buffer; compute SHA-256 of scope_bytes.
  4. Generate random 16-byte nonce.
  5. Compose 72-byte payload.
  6. Sign payload using signature_sign on the private key.
  7. Allocate Capability struct, store all fields.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(scope_length + sign).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The Capability is unforgeable under the unforgeability of Ed25519
(EUF-CMA per RFC 8032 / Bernstein 2011).

The issuing PRIVATE key must be protected per the PrivateKey discipline
(see private_key.runa). The compromise of the issuing key compromises
ALL capabilities issued under that key, retroactively.

Operation IDs and scopes are application-defined; the cryptographic
binding ensures they cannot be tampered with after issuance.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "capability_grant" takes arena as Integer, issuing_private_key as Integer, operation_id as Integer, scope_bytes as Integer, scope_length as Integer, issued_at as Integer, expiration as Integer returns Integer:
    If arena is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If issuing_private_key is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If scope_bytes is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If scope_length is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If expiration is less than issued_at:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let alg be SK.private_key_algorithm(issuing_private_key)
    If alg is not equal to Alg.ALG_ED25519:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let scope_hash be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, CAP_SCOPE_HASH_SIZE)
    If scope_hash is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let rh be Sha2.sha256_hash(arena, scope_bytes, scope_length, scope_hash)
    If rh is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let nonce_buf be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, CAP_NONCE_SIZE)
    If nonce_buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let rn be Entropy.entropy_random_bytes(arena, nonce_buf, CAP_NONCE_SIZE)
    If rn is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let payload be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, CAP_PAYLOAD_SIZE)
    If payload is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let enc_rc be capability_encode_payload(operation_id, scope_hash, issued_at, expiration, nonce_buf, payload)
    If enc_rc is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let sig_val be Sig.signature_sign(arena, issuing_private_key, payload, CAP_PAYLOAD_SIZE)
    If sig_val is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let cap be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, CAPABILITY_STRUCT_SIZE)
    If cap is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_qword(cap, CAP_OFF_OPERATION, operation_id)
    Memory.memory_set_qword(cap, CAP_OFF_SCOPE_HASH, scope_hash)
    Memory.memory_set_qword(cap, CAP_OFF_ISSUED_AT, issued_at)
    Memory.memory_set_qword(cap, CAP_OFF_EXPIRATION, expiration)
    Memory.memory_set_qword(cap, CAP_OFF_NONCE, nonce_buf)
    Memory.memory_set_qword(cap, CAP_OFF_SIGNATURE, sig_val)
    Return cap
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SECTION 3: capability_verify - cryptographic + temporal check
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Verify that the Capability:
  (a) was signed by issuing_public_key
  (b) covers the named operation_id
  (c) covers the supplied scope_bytes (i.e., SHA-256(scope) matches
      the embedded scope_hash)
  (d) has not yet expired (current_time < expiration)
  (e) was issued in the past (current_time >= issued_at)

Returns 1 if all checks pass, 0 otherwise.

Per HC#11 the signature check uses signature_verify, which itself
enforces the algorithm-match-public-key gate. So the entire chain
of cryptographic preconditions for trusting this capability is
type-safe.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Steps:
  1. Validate inputs.
  2. Check temporal bounds.
  3. Verify operation_id matches.
  4. Recompute scope_hash, constant-time compare.
  5. Re-encode payload and verify the embedded signature.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(scope_length + verify) ~ a few hundred microseconds for typical
scope lengths.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The cryptographic binding (Ed25519 signature) is the unforgeability
guarantee. The temporal and operation-match checks are policy checks;
violating them returns 0 just as a forged signature would.

References:
- RFC 8032 EUF-CMA guarantee for Ed25519.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "capability_verify" takes arena as Integer, cap as Integer, issuing_public_key as Integer, operation_id as Integer, scope_bytes as Integer, scope_length as Integer, current_time as Integer returns Integer:
    If arena is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If cap is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If issuing_public_key is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If scope_bytes is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Algorithm check.
    Let pk_alg be PK.public_key_algorithm(issuing_public_key)
    If pk_alg is not equal to Alg.ALG_ED25519:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Temporal.
    Let issued_at be Memory.memory_get_qword(cap, CAP_OFF_ISSUED_AT)
    Let expiration be Memory.memory_get_qword(cap, CAP_OFF_EXPIRATION)
    If current_time is less than issued_at:
        Return 0
    End If
    If current_time is greater than or equal to expiration:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Operation match.
    Let cap_op be Memory.memory_get_qword(cap, CAP_OFF_OPERATION)
    If cap_op is not equal to operation_id:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Recompute scope hash and constant-time compare.
    Let scope_hash_expected be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, CAP_SCOPE_HASH_SIZE)
    If scope_hash_expected is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let rh be Sha2.sha256_hash(arena, scope_bytes, scope_length, scope_hash_expected)
    If rh is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cap_scope_hash be Memory.memory_get_qword(cap, CAP_OFF_SCOPE_HASH)
    Let hash_match be Secure.constant_time_compare(scope_hash_expected, cap_scope_hash, CAP_SCOPE_HASH_SIZE)
    If hash_match is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Re-encode payload and verify signature.
    Let nonce_buf be Memory.memory_get_qword(cap, CAP_OFF_NONCE)
    Let payload be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, CAP_PAYLOAD_SIZE)
    If payload is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let enc_rc be capability_encode_payload(cap_op, cap_scope_hash, issued_at, expiration, nonce_buf, payload)
    If enc_rc is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let sig_val be Memory.memory_get_qword(cap, CAP_OFF_SIGNATURE)
    Return Sig.signature_verify(arena, issuing_public_key, payload, CAP_PAYLOAD_SIZE, sig_val)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SECTION 4: Accessors
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Returns the operation id from the capability.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Reads qword at offset 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Non-secret metadata.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "capability_operation_id" takes cap as Integer returns Integer:
    If cap is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return Memory.memory_get_qword(cap, CAP_OFF_OPERATION)
End Process

@Reasoning
Returns the issued_at timestamp.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Reads qword at offset 16.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Non-secret metadata.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "capability_issued_at" takes cap as Integer returns Integer:
    If cap is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return Memory.memory_get_qword(cap, CAP_OFF_ISSUED_AT)
End Process

@Reasoning
Returns the expiration timestamp.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Reads qword at offset 24.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Non-secret metadata.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "capability_expiration" takes cap as Integer returns Integer:
    If cap is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return Memory.memory_get_qword(cap, CAP_OFF_EXPIRATION)
End Process

@Reasoning
Returns the embedded signature pointer (a Signature value).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Reads qword at offset 40.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The signature is non-secret; transporting the capability includes
transporting its signature.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "capability_signature" takes cap as Integer returns Integer:
    If cap is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return Memory.memory_get_qword(cap, CAP_OFF_SIGNATURE)
End Process
